cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with learning landmark detectors for visual objects, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a method for learning without manual supervision, which falls under the category of unsupervised learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also introduces a tight bottleneck in the geometry-extraction process, which involves feature selection, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. The paper deals with generating images, which falls under the category of computer graphics, making cs.GR (Graphics) another possible category. Finally, the paper applies the proposed method to a variety of datasets, including faces, people, 3D objects, and digits, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
